  "title": "ISic000157. Funerary epitaph for Coponia",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"dis\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"dis\">d(is)</span>  <span data-text=\"manibus\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"manes\">m(anibus)</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Coponia Am\n                    emta\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Coponia\"><span data-text=\"Coponia\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Coponia\">Coponia</span></span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Am\n                    emta\"><span data-text=\"Am\n                    emta\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Amemta\">Am-<br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>[em]ta</span></span></span> · <span data-text=\"vixit\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"vivo\">v(ixit)</span> · <span data-text=\"annis\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"annus\">an(nis)</span> · <span data-text=\"L\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"L\">L</span> · </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"dis\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"dis\">dis</span>  <span data-text=\"manibus\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"manes\">manibus</span>  <span data-text=\"Coponia\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Coponia\">Coponia</span>  <span data-text=\"Amemta\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Amemta\">Amemta</span>  <span data-text=\"vixit\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"vivo\">vixit</span>  <span data-text=\"annis\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"annus\">annis</span>  <span data-text=\"L\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"L\">L</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"dis\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"dis\">D</span><span data-text=\"manibus\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"manes\">M</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Coponia Am\n                    emta\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Coponia\"><span data-text=\"Coponia\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Coponia\">COPONIA</span></span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Am\n                    emta\"><span data-text=\"Am\n                    emta\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Amemta\">AM<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>[..]TA</span></span></span>·<span data-text=\"vixit\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"vivo\">V</span>·<span data-text=\"annis\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"annus\">AN</span>·<span data-text=\"L\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"L\">L</span>·</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"dis\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"dis\">DIS</span><span data-text=\"manibus\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"manes\">MANIBUS</span><span data-text=\"Coponia\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Coponia\">COPONIA</span><span data-text=\"Amemta\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Amemta\">AMEMTA</span><span data-text=\"vixit\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"vivo\">VIXIT</span><span data-text=\"annis\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"annus\">ANNIS</span><span data-text=\"L\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"L\">L</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic000157_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.\" src=\"ISic000157_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000157.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.\" src=\"ISic000157-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic000157_rear_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.\" src=\"ISic000157_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000157_rear.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.\" src=\"ISic000157_rear-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text on basis of autopsy</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8417-7089\">Tuuli Ahlholm</a></p>  <p>To the Shades of the Underworld. Coponia Amemta lived 50 years.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Ferrua suggests that the full restoration of the missing cognomen from lines 2-3 is Amemta, which is of Greek origin, and which is rare, but is more commonly found in the masculine form (Amemptos), deriving from the adjective commonly found in contemporary Greek funerary inscriptions in Sicily. There are two other attestations of members of the gens Coponia from Thermae Himeraeae, see <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000156\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000156</a> and <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000158\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000158</a>, and another attestation from Messana, see <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000273\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000273</a>. As Bivona (1994) stresses, the gens Coponia is represented by a handful of republican senators and one equestrian procurator of Judaea under Augustus.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 1994.0777 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283</a>  </li><li> 1977.0339 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283</a>  </li><li> 78 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137</a>  </li><li> Ferrua 1941 262 no.22 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
